The paper deals with signal identification in communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. However, given the focus on identifying specific types of signals in a wireless communication system, it is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The use of statistical methods and analysis also suggests that it could belong to the Statistics (cs.ST) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the absence of channel or noise power estimation, which suggests that it could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.COMM, followed by cs.SI, cs.NI, and cs.LG.
